# Backend type safety (Postgres ↔ TypeScript)

Bridge [`src/services/supabase/types.ts`](../../src/services/supabase/types.ts) (DB row shapes) and [`src/types/domain.ts`](../../src/types/domain.ts) (app model) without mixing them at boundaries.

## No cross-leakage

- Do not expose `*Row` types or raw Supabase rows to UI, Zustand slices, or generic domain helpers. Convert via [`src/services/supabase/mappers.ts`](../../src/services/supabase/mappers.ts) or a dedicated mapper next to the RPC/service.

```typescript
// BAD: returning MatchRow from a hook used by screens for domain logic
// GOOD: map to Match / Player / … before leaving the service layer
```

- Do not pass domain objects directly into `.insert()` / `.update()` payloads. Map fields to DB column names and enum strings expected by Postgres (`rsvpToDb`, row-shaped builders, etc.).

## RPC return types

- For every `supabase.rpc(...)`, define an explicit TypeScript type or interface for the success payload (reuse a `*Row` from `types.ts` when the shape matches; otherwise add a dedicated name, e.g. `RpcGetMatchByJoinCodeRow`).
- Avoid leaving results as `unknown` or an untyped `as` cast. Narrow casts are acceptable when the declared target type is explicit (named).

